{
  "doc_id": "39532",
  "text": "Interpersonal networks can be considered as an asset, and as such, can be put to creative or destructive use, or even be left unused. Some interpersonal networks always exist but may remain inactive. However, agents will resort to their use more frequently, and also form new interpersonal networks, when impersonal markets are suppressed or weak, rent seeking behaviour is prevalent, and rules and laws are dysfunctional [CITATION_1] .",
